<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title><%= title %></title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/global.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/faq.css">
</head>
<body>
    <%- include('partials/header') %>

    <main class="main-content">
        <section class="faq-section">
            <div class="container">
                <h1 class="page-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
                <p class="page-subtitle">Find answers to common questions about our community portal</p>
                
                <div class="faq-container">
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <div class="faq-question">
                            <h3>What is the Local Community Portal?</h3>
                            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <p>The Local Community Portal is a comprehensive platform designed to connect residents with local events, activities, and services. It serves as a central hub where community members can discover what's happening in their area, register for events, and access various community resources across different interest areas including sports, health, education, arts & culture, environment, and social services.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <div class="faq-question">
                            <h3>How can I register for community events?</h3>
                            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <p>You can register for events in several ways:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Use the "Event Registration" quick link on our homepage</li>
                                <li>Click on specific events in the community areas section</li>
                                <li>Contact us directly through our contact form</li>
                                <li>Call our community center at (44) 888-8890</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p>Some events require advance registration while others accept walk-ins. Check individual event details for specific requirements.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <div class="faq-question">
                            <h3>Who can participate in community events and activities?</h3>
                            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <p>All local residents are welcome to participate in community events and activities. Most events are free and open to all ages, though some programs may have specific requirements such as:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Age restrictions for certain activities (e.g., senior fitness programs)</li>
                                <li>Skill level requirements for workshops</li>
                                <li>Pre-registration for events with limited capacity</li>
                                <li>Proof of residency for some subsidized programs</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <div class="faq-question">
                            <h3>How do I get involved as a volunteer?</h3>
                            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <p>We always welcome volunteers! You can get involved by:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Filling out our volunteer application through the contact form</li>
                                <li>Attending our monthly volunteer orientation sessions</li>
                                <li>Contacting our volunteer coordinator directly</li>
                                <li>Joining specific community area volunteer groups</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p>Volunteer opportunities range from event assistance to ongoing program support in areas like education tutoring, environmental cleanup, and social services.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <div class="faq-question">
                            <h3>Are there fees for community programs and events?</h3>
                            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <p>Most community events and basic programs are free for residents. However, some specialized programs may have fees to cover materials or instructor costs:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Arts and crafts workshops (materials fee)</li>
                                <li>Professional development seminars</li>
                                <li>Specialized fitness classes</li>
                                <li>Educational courses with certification</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p>We strive to keep all fees affordable and offer sliding scale pricing for those who need financial assistance.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <div class="faq-question">
                            <h3>How can I suggest new events or programs?</h3>
                            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <p>We love hearing from community members! You can suggest new events or programs by:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Using our contact form to submit detailed suggestions</li>
                                <li>Attending monthly community meetings (first Tuesday of each month)</li>
                                <li>Speaking with area coordinators during events</li>
                                <li>Participating in our annual community needs survey</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p>All suggestions are reviewed by our community planning committee and we'll follow up with you about feasibility and implementation.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <div class="faq-question">
                            <h3>Is the website mobile-friendly?</h3>
                            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <p>Yes! Our Community Portal website is fully responsive and optimized for mobile devices, tablets, and desktop computers. You can access all features and information from any device with an internet connection. While we don't currently have a dedicated mobile app, our website provides a seamless mobile experience.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <div class="faq-question">
                            <h3>How do I stay updated on community news and events?</h3>
                            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <p>Stay connected with our community through:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Regular visits to our website for updated event listings</li>
                                <li>Following us on social media (Facebook, Twitter, Instagram)</li>
                                <li>Subscribing to our monthly newsletter</li>
                                <li>Joining area-specific email lists</li>
                                <li>Attending community meetings</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <div class="faq-question">
                            <h3>What safety measures are in place for community events?</h3>
                            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <p>The safety of our community members is our top priority. We implement:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Certified first aid personnel at all major events</li>
                                <li>Safety briefings for physical activities</li>
                                <li>Background checks for all volunteers working with children</li>
                                <li>Emergency contact collection for all participants</li>
                                <li>Regular safety inspections of facilities and equipment</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <div class="faq-question">
                            <h3>How can I contact the Community Portal team?</h3>
                            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <p>You can reach us through multiple channels:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>Online:</strong> Use our contact form for general inquiries</li>
                                <li><strong>Phone:</strong> (44) 888-8890 (Mon-Fri, 9AM-5PM)</li>
                                <li><strong>Email:</strong> info@communityportal.org</li>
                                <li><strong>In Person:</strong> 123 Community Street, during business hours</li>
                                <li><strong>Social Media:</strong> Message us on Facebook, Twitter, or Instagram</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>

    <%- include('partials/footer') %>

    <script src="/js/script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>